properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 12 at 2:58PM CST until February 13 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...AN ARCTIC COLD FRONT WILL BRING SNOW, WIND AND MUCH COLDER
TEMPERATURES TO THE REGION...

.An arctic cold front will bring a widespread 1 to 2 inches of
snow to most of the forecast area. Locally higher amounts up to 3
inches can be expected in northwest Vilas County and the Fox
Valley and lakeshore areas. Gusty north winds and much colder air
will arrive in the wake of the front. The strongest winds will
develop in the Fox Valley and lakeshore areas, where gusts to
30 to 35 mph will result in areas of blowing and drifting snow
overnight. Wet roads will flash freeze as the arctic air arrives,
leading to the potential for black ice.

The combination of cold temperatures and winds will result in
wind chills as low as 20 below to 25 below zero over north
central and parts of central Wisconsin late tonight into Thursday
morning.

Motorists should anticipate hazardous travel conditions tonight,
especially in the Fox Valley and lakeshore areas. Anyone planning
outdoor activities should dress in layers and cover exposed skin
to avoid the risk of frostbite.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 3 inches.
Winds gusting as high as 30 to 35 mph, causing areas of blowing
and drifting snow overnight. Rapidly falling temperatures may
cause wet roads to flash freeze, leading to areas of black ice.

* WHERE...Portions of east central and northeast Wisconsin.

* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to 6 AM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on hazardous travel conditions, with snow or ice
covered roads. Areas of blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility in open areas, especially on west to east oriented
roads.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for Wisconsin can be obtained by
calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM CST THURSDAY
